Job Title: Software Engineer II - Money Data Insights
Location: San Francisco, CA 94103 (South of Market area)
Description:
As a Backend Engineer at Uber, you’ll be working on code that’s closest to the business. You will build user-facing products, handle and store thousands of payment transactions per second, and develop intelligent fraud prevention strategies that scale. From building maps that help move millions of people, to the messaging systems that let us interact with them - the work you do will impact live riders, eaters, drivers, and operations teams across the globe.
About the Role
As a backend engineer on the Money Data Insights team, you will be responsible for building and maintaining systems, which the teams across the company use to get payments related data to fulfill their reporting and compliance needs, while collaborating extensively with those teams to anticipate platform features required to enable them to launch new and innovative products.
What You'll Do
Responsible for delivery of high quality features that address business needs at very high scale.
Collaborate closely with stakeholders, product, and other engineering teams.
Test, monitor and safely deploy features.
Basic Qualifications
At least two (2) years of software engineering experience
Bachelor of Science (BS) in Computer Science, Physics, or Mathematics, or related field
Experience coding with Go, Java, Python, or C++
Strong problem solving and coding skills
Experience with developing, debugging, and shipping software products on large code bases that span platforms and tools
Experience with Software Development processes such as design, planning, implementation, maintenance & documentation
Demonstrated experience working collaboratively in cross-functional teams
Passion for learning new technologies, domains, and challenging the status quo.
Grit, drive and a strong feeling of ownership coupled with collaboration.
Preferred Qualifications
Experience with distributed storage and database systems (SQL or NoSQL, e.g. MySQL, Dynamo, Cassandra).
Experience with building high performance, scalable distributed systems using technologies like Kafka, Hadoop, Hive, or Zookeeper
Experience with production-quality services, deployment, monitoring, and reliability.
Ability to decompose complex business problems into clean, extensible, performant services and systems.
Self driven to identify opportunities to make things better and efficient.
Customer focus and a drive to support different businesses at a platform level.
Background with payment systems or financial technology.

Job ID: 54144 Data Engineer
Our client is seeking a Data Engineer on a project that will help to lay the foundational components to improve Data Quality, Data Integrity, and utilization of Data as an Asset. This project is part of a broader strategic roadmap to modernize the Data foundations and Analytics capabilities by delivering on an upgrade program from SAP ECC to SAP S/4 Hana.

Responsibilities
Support requirements of digital initiatives by delivery of the shared, reusable data platform and integration capabilities.
Facilitate faster solution development, maintenance and customization and overall time to deliver
Increase transparency and supportability of integrations and data platforms.
Improve resilience and scalability of data pipeline, data platform, and related integrations.
Manage data flows between applications and the Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) in an efficient and thorough manner.
Reduce technical debt resulting from the current data pipeline middleware solutions.
Increase the scope and trustworthiness of historical data in EDW.
Provide a Minimum Viable Foundation to enable dependent workstreams to leverage these elements as the Data Platform continues to expand over time.
The Data Engineer will be accountable for understanding the business goals and understanding of the business use cases, championing the stakeholders objectives and overseeing the activities of a system integrator to ensure proper adherence to IT governance and SDLC policy during planning, development, integration, testing, and implementation activities during the upgrade from SAP ECC to SAP S/4
Scope (High Level)
To build a data management platform to catalog the data, profile the data for sharing, reuse and improve the data quality and data integrity of customer and relevant business functions data
To design and implement a new data architecture that leverages the existing Azure cloud platform to host a centralized, comprehensive Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) for all enterprise analytics and reporting use cases.
An EDW enables data journey from Data Information Insights Decisions

Deliverables The Data Engineer will collaborate with internal and System Integration partner to deliver:

Gather requirements, provide design, and implement solutions to extract data from source systems, and transform and load data into our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) in Azure cloud and on-premise.

Facilitate implementation and expansion of an enterprise data catalog solution.

Data profiling of key master and reference data objects identifying gaps and quality issues across software assets in scope.

Discover, Catalog, Profile and assess key SAP ECC master data attributes to provide an actionable and prioritized data quality/ data cleansing remediation plan

Assess and document security requirements from data privacy, confidentiality, and sensitivity aspects for the SAP ecosystem.

Understand and support data standards and processes to support master data migration

Prepare and/or update operating procedures and other documentation needed to support data migration activities.
Use appropriate practices, in accordance with SDLC policies and quality expectations.
Follow internal policies, standards, procedures, templates, and processes (i.e., forms, access requests, deliverables, etc.)
Work with and coordinate with internal resources, technical consultants, SMEs, System Integration (SI) partners and specialists in support of technical planning, design, and implementation.
Proper fit with internal relationship driven culture of customer focus, respect, accountability, and continues learning.
Assistance to project manager in overall project delivery by focusing on scoping, effort and resource estimating of technical tasks.
Establishment of quality targets and operational metrics for technical deliverables in accordance with SDLC policy.
Problem-solving/decision-making as needed by the project.

Qualifications
Bachelors Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent experience.
5+ years of experience as a Data Engineer or in a similar role.
Informatica development and administration experience.
Experience with data modeling, data warehousing, and building ETL pipelines
Experience in SQL

Minimum 3 to 5 years of technical experience in Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services (IICS)

Experience working with Informatica connectors for cloud-based and on-premises systems such as SAP and DB2i .
Experience with data warehouse ETL tools such as Informatica, Azure Data Factory, SSIS, stored procedures.
Experience with data modeling, data warehouse design, and building data marts and data pipelines
Strong knowledge of data fundamentals including data structures, algorithm design and complexity analysis.
Design and implement system modifications
Proficiency with RDBMS technology fundamentals, SQL, and Query optimization
Strong troubleshooting and diagnostic skills to determine and resolve issues.
Experience supporting, architecting, and designing requirements with respect to the flow of data between SAP and non-SAP systems preferred.
Knowledge and practical application of best practices for architecting, designing & supporting BI data platforms.
Ability to optimize the performance of enterprise business intelligence solutions by means redesigning or re-architecting data structures or data flows.

Experience working in the Microsoft Azure cloud environment.

Skills
Ability to elicit requirements and motivations of the business community through interviews, facilitated sessions and written correspondence
Demonstrate ability to effectively articulate technical challenges and solutions.

Basic knowledge and proficiency to write Data Definition Language or Data Manipulation Language SQL commands

Experience working with business areas and other non-technical groups, translating requests into requirements

Have the investigative mindset and/or techniques that can be used with any number of tools to explore the available data

Ability to understand and translate the need of business units into effective data management solutions.

Experience in data validation and ability to analyze large datasets.
Some hands-on experience with reporting / visualization tools is greatly desired.
Background in Gas Utilities industry preferred.
Understanding and knowledge of IT standards and controls, IT Service Management [ITSM, ITIL] methods.
Mature planning, organizational, and time management skills.
Excellent interpersonal skills, including collaboration, facilitation, and negotiation.

Job ID: 54144 Data Engineer
Our client is seeking a Data Engineer on a project that will help to lay the foundational components to improve Data Quality, Data Integrity, and utilization of Data as an Asset. This project is part of a broader strategic roadmap to modernize the Data foundations and Analytics capabilities by delivering on an upgrade program from SAP ECC to SAP S/4 Hana.

Responsibilities
Support requirements of digital initiatives by delivery of the shared, reusable data platform and integration capabilities.
Facilitate faster solution development, maintenance and customization and overall time to deliver
Increase transparency and supportability of integrations and data platforms.
Improve resilience and scalability of data pipeline, data platform, and related integrations.
Manage data flows between applications and the Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) in an efficient and thorough manner.
Reduce technical debt resulting from the current data pipeline middleware solutions.
Increase the scope and trustworthiness of historical data in EDW.
Provide a Minimum Viable Foundation to enable dependent workstreams to leverage these elements as the Data Platform continues to expand over time.
The Data Engineer will be accountable for understanding the business goals and understanding of the business use cases, championing the stakeholders objectives and overseeing the activities of a system integrator to ensure proper adherence to IT governance and SDLC policy during planning, development, integration, testing, and implementation activities during the upgrade from SAP ECC to SAP S/4
Scope (High Level)
To build a data management platform to catalog the data, profile the data for sharing, reuse and improve the data quality and data integrity of customer and relevant business functions data
To design and implement a new data architecture that leverages the existing Azure cloud platform to host a centralized, comprehensive Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) for all enterprise analytics and reporting use cases.
An EDW enables data journey from Data Information Insights Decisions

Deliverables The Data Engineer will collaborate with internal and System Integration partner to deliver:

Gather requirements, provide design, and implement solutions to extract data from source systems, and transform and load data into our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) in Azure cloud and on-premise.

Facilitate implementation and expansion of an enterprise data catalog solution.

Data profiling of key master and reference data objects identifying gaps and quality issues across software assets in scope.

Discover, Catalog, Profile and assess key SAP ECC master data attributes to provide an actionable and prioritized data quality/ data cleansing remediation plan

Assess and document security requirements from data privacy, confidentiality, and sensitivity aspects for the SAP ecosystem.

Understand and support data standards and processes to support master data migration

Prepare and/or update operating procedures and other documentation needed to support data migration activities.
Use appropriate practices, in accordance with SDLC policies and quality expectations.
Follow internal policies, standards, procedures, templates, and processes (i.e., forms, access requests, deliverables, etc.)
Work with and coordinate with internal resources, technical consultants, SMEs, System Integration (SI) partners and specialists in support of technical planning, design, and implementation.
Proper fit with internal relationship driven culture of customer focus, respect, accountability, and continues learning.
Assistance to project manager in overall project delivery by focusing on scoping, effort and resource estimating of technical tasks.
Establishment of quality targets and operational metrics for technical deliverables in accordance with SDLC policy.
Problem-solving/decision-making as needed by the project.

Qualifications
Bachelors Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or equivalent experience.
5+ years of experience as a Data Engineer or in a similar role.
Informatica development and administration experience.
Experience with data modeling, data warehousing, and building ETL pipelines
Experience in SQL

Minimum 3 to 5 years of technical experience in Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services (IICS)

Experience working with Informatica connectors for cloud-based and on-premises systems such as SAP and DB2i .
Experience with data warehouse ETL tools such as Informatica, Azure Data Factory, SSIS, stored procedures.
Experience with data modeling, data warehouse design, and building data marts and data pipelines
Strong knowledge of data fundamentals including data structures, algorithm design and complexity analysis.
Design and implement system modifications
Proficiency with RDBMS technology fundamentals, SQL, and Query optimization
Strong troubleshooting and diagnostic skills to determine and resolve issues.
Experience supporting, architecting, and designing requirements with respect to the flow of data between SAP and non-SAP systems preferred.
Knowledge and practical application of best practices for architecting, designing & supporting BI data platforms.
Ability to optimize the performance of enterprise business intelligence solutions by means redesigning or re-architecting data structures or data flows.

Experience working in the Microsoft Azure cloud environment.

Skills
Ability to elicit requirements and motivations of the business community through interviews, facilitated sessions and written correspondence
Demonstrate ability to effectively articulate technical challenges and solutions.

Basic knowledge and proficiency to write Data Definition Language or Data Manipulation Language SQL commands

Experience working with business areas and other non-technical groups, translating requests into requirements

Have the investigative mindset and/or techniques that can be used with any number of tools to explore the available data

Ability to understand and translate the need of business units into effective data management solutions.

Experience in data validation and ability to analyze large datasets.
Some hands-on experience with reporting / visualization tools is greatly desired.
Background in Gas Utilities industry preferred.
Understanding and knowledge of IT standards and controls, IT Service Management [ITSM, ITIL] methods.
Mature planning, organizational, and time management skills.
Excellent interpersonal skills, including collaboration, facilitation, and negotiation.
